Package: figsimR
Type: Package
Title: Simulating Fig Wasp Community Assembly
Version: 0.2.1
Author: Yiyi Dong
Maintainer: Yiyi Dong <dongyiyi09@hotmail.com>
Description: Simulates the assembly and structure of fig wasp communities 
    within fig fruits (Ficus racemosa), capturing ecological processes such as 
    entry order, parasitism, spatial oviposition constraints, resource limitation, 
    and fruit abortion. Designed for ecological modeling and hypothesis testing 
    using empirical parameters. Current version 0.2.1 is integrated with the "sink strength" theory.
    Added support for species-level `none` entries in `layer_preference`, allowing some species to 
    bypass the ovary-layer preference filter. Clarified that `layer_preference` refers to ovary-layer 
    preference or accessibility. Improved handling of user-defined 
    fig-wasp communities or other species interaction systems with custom species lists and species-specific parameter objects.
    Retained *Ficus racemosa*-specific defaults for the worked example while allowing users
    to override them with system-specific parameters.
